<MELItem itemNbr="21-52-07" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-21-52-07.1.2-21-52-07">
<Title>Pack Outlet Temperature Sensor Systems</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="1">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One may be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Associated flight deck duct temperature sensor operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Opposite air conditioning pack operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Opposite flight deck zone trim valve operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Opposite trim air pressure regulator valve operates normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>EDTO  is not conducted.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<Para>For an air conditioning pack to be operating normally, certain items associated with that system must operate normally.  See MEL item 21-51-01 for a list of those items.</Para>
</MaintenanceNote>
<OperationNote>
<Para>If cabin or flight deck temperatures become too cool, climbing to a higher altitude will increase the heating capability of the air conditioning system.</Para>
</OperationNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
